 Port Scanning & Enumeration
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand the fundamentals of port scanning and network enumeration
Use Nmap to discover open ports and services on local systems
Utilize Netcat for basic connection testing and service verification
Identify and analyze listening services on a Linux system
Interpret scan results to assess network security posture
Apply ethical hacking principles in a controlled environment
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic understanding of networking concepts (IP addresses, ports, protocols)
Familiarity with Linux command-line interface
Knowledge of TCP/IP protocol fundamentals
Understanding of common network services (HTTP, SSH, FTP, etc.)
Basic cybersecurity awareness and ethical considerations
